<%- include('partials/header') %>
<%- include('partials/nav') %>

<main id="main-content">
    <section class="section">
        <div class="container" style="max-width:800px;">
            <div class="section-header">
                <h2>Terms, Rules & Regulations</h2>
                <p>Please read these terms carefully before using BrightMinds Tutoring services.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="card" style="padding:40px;">
                <h3 style="margin-bottom:16px;color:var(--blue-700);">1. Session Policies</h3>
                <p style="color:var(--gray-600);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:12px;"><strong>Cancellation Policy:</strong> Sessions may be cancelled up to 24 hours in advance without penalty. Cancellations made less than 24 hours before a scheduled session will be marked as a late cancellation.</p>
                <p style="color:var(--gray-600);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:12px;"><strong>Late Cancellation Limit:</strong> Each student is allowed one late cancellation per billing cycle without penalty. Additional late cancellations within the same billing cycle may result in a fee equal to 50% of the session cost.</p>
                <p style="color:var(--gray-600);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:24px;"><strong>No-Shows:</strong> If a student does not appear for a scheduled session without prior notice, the session will be counted as used and will not be rescheduled.</p>

                <h3 style="margin-bottom:16px;color:var(--blue-700);">2. Tutor Responsibilities</h3>
                <p style="color:var(--gray-600);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:12px;"><strong>Missed Sessions by Tutors:</strong> If a tutor fails to attend a scheduled session, the session will be rescheduled at no cost to the student. If a tutor misses two or more sessions in a single month, the matter will be reviewed by management and may result in disciplinary action.</p>
                <p style="color:var(--gray-600);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:24px;"><strong>Session Reports:</strong> Tutors are required to complete a session sheet after each meeting, documenting topics covered, student performance, and plans for the next session.</p>

                <h3 style="margin-bottom:16px;color:var(--blue-700);">3. Payment and Billing</h3>
                <p style="color:var(--gray-600);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:12px;"><strong>Billing Cycle:</strong> Subscriptions are billed on a monthly basis. Payment is due on or before the billing date shown in your dashboard.</p>
                <p style="color:var(--gray-600);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:12px;"><strong>Payment Reminders:</strong> Parents and guardians will receive reminders via the platform and email when a payment is approaching. A text message reminder will also be sent when applicable.</p>
                <p style="color:var(--gray-600);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:12px;"><strong>Referral Discounts:</strong> Each user receives a unique referral code upon registration. When a new user signs up using a referral code, the new user receives a 10% discount on their first billing cycle. Referral codes cannot be stacked or combined with other promotions.</p>
                <p style="color:var(--gray-600);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:24px;"><strong>Charity Contribution:</strong> 3% of every payment is donated to the <%= charityName %>. This is included in your subscription price and is not an additional charge.</p>

                <h3 style="margin-bottom:16px;color:var(--blue-700);">4. Subscription Cancellation</h3>
                <p style="color:var(--gray-600);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:12px;">You may cancel your subscription at any time through your parent/guardian dashboard. Cancellation takes effect at the end of the current billing cycle. No refunds are provided for partial months.</p>
                <p style="color:var(--gray-600);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:24px;">To cancel, navigate to your dashboard and select "Cancel Subscription." You will be asked to provide a reason for cancellation to help us improve our services.</p>

                <h3 style="margin-bottom:16px;color:var(--blue-700);">5. Code of Conduct</h3>
                <p style="color:var(--gray-600);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:12px;">All users, including students, parents, and tutors, are expected to maintain a respectful and professional environment. Harassment, discrimination, or abusive behavior of any kind will not be tolerated and may result in immediate account termination.</p>
                <p style="color:var(--gray-600);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:24px;">All communication between tutors and students should take place through the BrightMinds platform or during scheduled sessions. Personal contact information should not be exchanged without parental consent.</p>

                <h3 style="margin-bottom:16px;color:var(--blue-700);">6. Check-Ins</h3>
                <p style="color:var(--gray-600);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:24px;">BrightMinds conducts check-ins every 3 months for every active student. These check-ins are designed to review progress, address any concerns, and ensure the tutoring relationship is working well. The platform will send automated alerts to remind the team when check-ins are due.</p>

                <h3 style="margin-bottom:16px;color:var(--blue-700);">7. Privacy and Data</h3>
                <p style="color:var(--gray-600);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:12px;">BrightMinds Tutoring takes your privacy seriously. Personal information is collected only for the purpose of providing tutoring services and is never sold to third parties.</p>
                <p style="color:var(--gray-600);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:24px;">Session data, progress reports, and communications are stored securely and accessible only to authorized users (the student, their parent/guardian, their tutor, and BrightMinds administration).</p>

                <h3 style="margin-bottom:16px;color:var(--blue-700);">8. Modifications</h3>
                <p style="color:var(--gray-600);line-height:1.8;">BrightMinds reserves the right to update these terms at any time. Users will be notified of significant changes via email. Continued use of the platform after changes are posted constitutes acceptance of the updated terms.</p>

                <div style="margin-top:32px;padding:20px;background:var(--blue-50);border-radius:var(--radius);text-align:center;">
                    <p style="color:var(--gray-600);font-weight:600;">Questions about our terms? <a href="/contact">Contact us</a> and we will be happy to help.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</main>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
